Park Factors

<< 6/18 June 19, 2025 6/20 >>

Last Updated: 11:09 AM

More excellent hitting conditions are in store for Thursday with most games featuring warm temperatures and out-blowing wind. Some of the best conditions on the slate are in Nationals Park and Yankee Stadium where it will be in the 90s this afternoon with double-digit wind blowing out. The venue in The Bronx is a bit more receptive to wind than the one in D.C. is.

Temperatures will cool down a bit from yesterday's scorcher at Sutter Health, but the typical outward wind is expected to blow a bit harder. SHP has shown to be highly impacted by wind so far this season and the 15-20 mph gusts figure to come into play for Astros / Athletics tonight.

Great American Ball Park is rated the top scoring environment on Thursday's slate. The weather is only contributing moderately, however, with temps in the 70s and a 10 mph wind that isn't very influential given the stadium. The small outfield at GABP is the primary factor for today's rating with the decent conditions providing a boost. This one has been flagged for possibly delay with a chance of rain in Cincinnati this afternoon.

Thursday's doubleheaders in Detroit (PIT / DET) and Chicago (STL / CHW) will feature temps in the 60s and 70s, respectively, with out-blowing wind expected for each. Comerica Park is a bit more receptive to wind than Rate Field is, but the outfield is larger.

As usual, the out-blowing wind at Oracle Park can be ignored as the pattern is typical for just about every Giants home game with little impact.

Several games are flagged for possible delay/PPD as indicated by the pink highlights below.
